About the Series:
The series is primarily set in Yorkshire, and follows the work of two detectives that are 
thrown together as partners.
Episodes in this series are divided on on the DVDs into part 1 and part 2 but I have encoded
these together to give the original episode as broadcast, so don't be supprised at credits
at 45 minutes in, as the whole episode is there and all episodes are approx 100 minutes. 

Episode 1 "Houdini's Ghost"
Retired entrepreneur Pal McLean is found dead in his study, with his face having been shot 
to a pulp by a shotgun.

Episode 2 "Glory Days"
The driver of Wetherton Wanderers F.C.'s tour bus, Ben Hawkins, mysteriously stops the bus 
in the middle of train tracks, causing the death of three people.

Episode 3 "Wrong Time, Wrong Place"
Dalziel and Pascoe are invited over to Amsterdam for a police conference from Dutch 
Superintendent De Kuiper, on the morals of people trafficking and prostitution.

Episode 4 "Guardian Angel"
Housewife Susan Goodman is poisoned to death whilst in the course of doing her weekly 
shopping. Initially suspected as a terrorist attack.

Episode 5 "A Death in the Family"
Security guard Dave Compton is murdered in a high-stakes, high reward transit depot 
robbery, in which the robbers get away with Â£600,000 pounds.
